<h3>Query Volume Growth</h3>
<p>Perplexity alone grew from 230 million queries in mid-2024 to 780 million by May 2025. That is a 3x increase in under a year.</p>
<p>Google AI Overviews went from appearing on <a href="https://www.superlines.io/articles/ai-search-statistics/">13.14% of searches in March 2025 to 25.11%</a> one year later. At this pace, AI-generated answers will appear on the majority of informational searches by late 2026.</p>
<h3>AI Referral Traffic</h3>
<p>AI referral traffic now accounts for <a href="https://www.superlines.io/articles/ai-search-statistics/">1.08% of all website traffic</a> and grows approximately 1% month over month. That sounds small until you consider the scale. For a site receiving 100,000 monthly visits, that is 1,080 visits from AI sources alone, and growing.</p>
<p>ChatGPT drives 87.4% of that AI referral traffic. Perplexity drives most of the remainder. Google AI Overviews send minimal direct referral traffic because users stay within Google.</p>
<p>The trend is clear. AI search user bases are expanding rapidly. Query volumes are doubling and tripling. And websites that earn AI citations capture a growing share of a new traffic source.</p>
<h2>Chapter 3: How AI Overviews Are Reshaping Click Behavior</h2>
<p>The most disruptive change is what happens to clicks. AI Overviews do not just add a new element to search results. They absorb the clicks that used to go to organic listings.</p>
<h3>Zero-Click Search Rates</h3>
<p>Zero-click searches now exceed <a href="https://click-vision.com/zero-click-search-statistics">65% in Q1 2026</a>, up from 58% in November 2025. For queries that trigger AI Overviews specifically, the zero-click rate hits 80-83%.</p>
<p>Google AI Mode sessions are even more extreme. <a href="https://www.superlines.io/articles/ai-search-statistics/">93% of AI Mode sessions</a> end without a single click to an external website.</p>
<p>Mobile search amplifies this. Approximately <a href="https://heroicrankings.com/seo/managed/google-ai-overview-statistics-2026/">81% of AI Overview triggers</a> happen on mobile devices, where screen space makes the AI answer even more dominant.</p>
<h3>CTR Impact on Organic Results</h3>
<p>Organic click-through rates dropped <a href="https://www.dataslayer.ai/blog/google-ai-overviews-the-end-of-traditional-ctr-and-how-to-adapt-in-2025">61% for queries with AI Overviews</a>, falling from 1.76% to 0.61%. That is a steep decline.</p>
<p>Some websites report <a href="https://heroicrankings.com/seo/managed/google-ai-overview-statistics-2026/">search traffic drops of 20-40%</a> since AI Overviews expanded. News publishers took the hardest hit. Organic visits fell from 2.3 billion in mid-2024 to under 1.7 billion by mid-2025 across major publishers.</p>
<h3>The Citation Advantage</h3>
<p>There is a counterbalance. Brands cited in AI Overviews earn <a href="https://thedigitalbloom.com/learn/organic-traffic-crisis-report-2026-update/">35% more organic clicks</a> than those not cited. Being named as a source in an AI answer actually boosts your traditional organic performance.</p>
<p>This creates a two-tier system. Cited brands gain both AI visibility and organic traffic. Uncited brands lose clicks to the AI answer and get nothing in return.</p>
